===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|雈|臼|c1=s|c2=p|t1=owl|ls=psc}}.

Originally refers to a type of owl; later {{Han phonetically borrowed}} for a homophonous word meaning "old." The upper portion frequently appears as {{zh-l|*萑}} (a type of grass).

===Etymology 1===
Possibly from {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*(g/k)əw-n||elder brother; senior male relative}}, which is also compared to {{och-l|舅|maternal uncle}}, {{och-l|昆|elder brother}} ({{zh-ref|Sagart, 1999}}; STEDT).

{{zh-ref|Baxter and Sagart (2014)}} compares it to {{och-l|久|tr=*[k]ʷəʔ}}. See there for more.

